parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to not retract properly, rendering it inoperative and increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract
the plastic cover or female portion of the buckle detaches
the seat belt buckle plastic latch plate breaks
the seat belt does not lock up during impact
the seat belt locks the occupant in and does not release.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Defective CV joints can cause noise, vibration, and loss of control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Transmission lockup or failure can cause sudden stops, loss of control, and accidents, putting the driver and passengers at risk.
Corrosion of transmission bolts can cause the transmission to fall out, leading to loss of control and accidents.
Torque converter failure can cause sudden stops, loss of control, and accidents, putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Vehicle comes to an abrupt stop

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transaxle fluid leak or damage can cause the transmission to freeze, leading to loss of control and accidents.
Frame misalignment can cause uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and increased risk of accidents.
Door misalignment and handle failure can cause difficulty entering or exiting the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
Failure of the rear hatch hydraulic units can cause the hatch to fall, potentially injuring individuals or causing damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Rear hatch does not stay open
difficulty opening or closing the rear hatch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the hood latch can cause the hood to fly open while driving, potentially obstructing the driver's view and causing accidents.
symptoms: damage to the windshield and hood
difficulty opening or closing the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Cooling system failure can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, or loss of power.
Exhaust system failure can cause the vehicle to emit excessive noise, reduce performance, and potentially lead to carbon monoxide poisoning.
symptoms: excessive noise from the exhaust system.
